{"image_id": "PMC5923374_9", "image_size": [708, 1000], "ocr": [{"text": "Cancers 2018, 10, 119 10 of 14", "bbox": [90.6, 65.9, 616.2, 77.7]}, {"text": "4. Materials and Methods", "bbox": [90.9, 105.2, 229.0, 119.8]}, {"text": "4.1. Cell Lines and Cell Culture Conditions", "bbox": [90.9, 132.7, 298.6, 147.4]}, {"text": "Human embryonic kidney (HEK) 293T cells were maintained in Dulbecco’s minimal essential", "bbox": [116.2, 155.8, 616.2, 170.3]}, {"text": "medium (DMEM, Gibco, Waltham, MA, USA) supplemented with 10% fetal bovine serum (FBS),", "bbox": [90.9, 171.8, 617.6, 186.3]}, {"text": "100 units/mL penicillin, and 100 µg/mL streptomycin sulfate (P/S). The EBV-positive nasopharyngeal", "bbox": [90.3, 187.9, 616.2, 202.4]}, {"text": "epithelial (NPE) cell lines NP361hTERT-EBV and NP460hTERT-EBV were grown in a 1:1 mixture of", "bbox": [90.9, 203.9, 616.2, 218.4]}, {"text": "Deﬁned Keratinocyte-SFM (Gibco) and Epilife™ medium (Gibco) with 1% P/S. The EBV-positive NPC", "bbox": [90.9, 220.0, 616.2, 234.5]}, {"text": "cell line C666-1 was grown in RPMI-1640 medium (Gibco) supplemented with 10% FBS and 1% P/S,", "bbox": [90.9, 236.0, 617.6, 250.5]}, {"text": "and the EBV-positive gastric carcinoma cell line AGS-BX1 was cultured in F-12K Nutrient mixture", "bbox": [90.9, 252.1, 616.2, 266.6]}, {"text": "(Gibco) supplemented with 10% FBS and 1% P/S. The cell lines NP460hTERT-EBV and AGS-BX1 were", "bbox": [90.5, 268.1, 616.2, 282.6]}, {"text": "stimulated for 16 h with 0.5 µg/mL poly(I:C) (Invitrogen, Waltham, MA, USA), and NP361hTERT-EBV", "bbox": [90.9, 284.2, 616.6, 298.7]}, {"text": "was stimulated for 16 h with 1 µg/mL poly(I:C) (Invitrogen). C666-1 cells were treated for 48 h with", "bbox": [90.4, 300.2, 616.2, 314.7]}, {"text": "0.2 mM PS-1145 (Santa Cruz Biotechnology, Dallas, TX, USA) to inhibit NF-κB activity. All cells were", "bbox": [90.9, 316.2, 616.2, 330.8]}, {"text": "cultured at 37 ◦C with 5% CO2.", "bbox": [90.9, 331.9, 254.0, 348.2]}, {"text": "4.2. Plasmid Constructs", "bbox": [90.9, 359.9, 206.9, 374.6]}, {"text": "The Qp reporter plasmid was constructed by cloning the −100 to +36 Qp DNA sequence described", "bbox": [116.2, 383.0, 616.2, 406.0]}, {"text": "previously into the pGL2 (Amersham Pharmacia, Amersham, Buckinghamshire, UK) luciferase", "bbox": [90.6, 399.1, 616.2, 413.6]}, {"text": "reporter plasmid [39]. The pcDNA3.1-EGFP expression vectors expressing NF-κB p50 and p65 have", "bbox": [90.9, 415.1, 616.2, 429.6]}, {"text": "also been described previously. Mutagenesis of the Qp promoter was performed using the QuikChange", "bbox": [90.9, 431.2, 616.2, 445.7]}, {"text": "site-directed mutagenesis kit (Stratagene, La Jolla, CA, USA) as described by the manufacturer. Primers", "bbox": [90.9, 447.2, 616.2, 461.7]}, {"text": "are listed in Table 1.", "bbox": [90.9, 463.2, 194.4, 477.8]}, {"text": "Table 1. Oligonucleotides used in this study.", "bbox": [248.8, 490.7, 457.9, 503.9]}, {"text": "Oligo Sequence (5′–3′)", "bbox": [215.1, 519.3, 461.5, 533.0]}, {"text": "BCL2L11-F CAAGAGTTGCGGCGTATTGGAG", "bbox": [162.0, 537.0, 457.5, 548.8]}, {"text": "BCL2L11-R ACACCAGGCGGACAATGTAACG", "bbox": [162.0, 548.8, 460.7, 560.5]}, {"text": "ChIP-Qp-F GACAGAAATTGGGTGACCACTGAGGG", "bbox": [162.0, 560.5, 488.8, 572.3]}, {"text": "ChIP-Qp-R CGCCATCCGGTAGCGCAC", "bbox": [162.0, 572.3, 429.7, 584.1]}, {"text": "ChIP-Control-F TCCCTAAGTCACTTTCTTCAAGTTGC", "bbox": [162.0, 584.1, 477.7, 595.8]}, {"text": "ChIP-Control-R CGTGCATTTAATTGTGTCTTGTGG", "bbox": [162.0, 595.8, 462.5, 607.6]}, {"text": "EBV-BLLF1-F TGTGCTGATAGAGGCTGGTG", "bbox": [162.0, 607.6, 441.7, 619.4]}, {"text": "EBV-BLLF1-R TGACACCAAGTCCATCTCCA", "bbox": [162.0, 619.4, 442.6, 631.1]}, {"text": "EBV-BMRF1-F AGGAGTGCTGCAGGTAAACC", "bbox": [162.0, 631.2, 446.1, 642.9]}, {"text": "EBV-BMRF1-R GCTCTGGTGATTCTGCCACT", "bbox": [162.0, 642.9, 438.7, 654.7]}, {"text": "EBV-BZLF1-F AAATTTAAGAGATCCTCGTGTAAAACATC", "bbox": [162.0, 654.7, 502.2, 666.4]}, {"text": "EBV-BZLF1-